Description: UberTags employs container tag technology to enable websites to dynamically deploy tags (code snippets) on their websites.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: UberTags built the easiest way to manage website tagging. Websites increasingly use code snippets called tags to make their websites run--tags are used for integrating analytics, marketing conversion tracking (pixels), surveys, video, widgets, A/B testing, live chat, and more.  As tag usage has increased, so has tagging pain. UberTags built a container tag solution that makes it dead-easy to manage website tagging. Site managers simply paste their UberTag across their site(s) and then deploy all other tagging right from a browser. So, for example, you can deploy conversion tags on your thank-you pages, live chat on your support site, A/B testing on your landing pages, and analytics and retargeting across every page of your site via a browser in just a few minutes.  Key benefits:  > Sites load faster! The core page loads then tags stream asynchronously. > Launch a tag in minutes instead of waiting for IT. > Centrally see your tags. See where a tag is loading and see which tags are loading on a particular page.

Description: Video Game Design & Research Lab
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Go Go Games Studios is a design studio and research lab that creates playful, innovative software for families of children (ages 4-10) on the autism spectrum.  The CDC estimates that 1 in 88 U.S. children has an autism spectrum disorder, up from 1 in 110 just a few years ago. This makes autism the fastest growing disability in the country.  The current gold standard of treatment is 25 to 40 hours a week of time-consuming and expensive one-on-one therapies - a burden that many families cannot shoulder. At the same time, children with autism spend twice as much time playing video games as typically developing children. We translate effective therapies into video games to provide therapeutic benefits to children who might otherwise not receive them. Go Go Games Studios strives to design therapeutic game experiences that delight and educate children with special needs. The founders believe that every child should be able to grow up to live a full, independent, and productive life, and they are deeply committed to helping a niche community where children too often do not see these outcomes.  On October 2011, Go Go Games was launched on the Apple App Store, featured as "New & Noteworthy". Since then, the company's inaugural product has received glowing reviews from Common Sense Media, Hack Education, and Autism Speaks, and is a recipient of the prestigious "Editor's Choice" Award for Excellence in Design from Children's Technology Review.
Founders: Alexis Hiniker, Heidi Williamson, Joy Wong Daniels
